      "audioScript": "I'll admit, I used to dread giving up my car and taking the bus to work. I pictured long waits in the cold and crowded seats. But six months in, I've completely changed my mind, and I'd encourage anyone on the fence to try it. The obvious win is money; between parking downtown, gas, and insurance, I was spending a small fortune. My monthly transit pass costs a fraction of that. But the benefit I've come to value most isn't financial at all, it's time. On the bus, I read, answer emails, or just stare out the window and let my mind wander. Driving, I was tense, gripping the wheel in traffic, arriving frazzled. Now I get to work calm and having actually finished a book. Sure, there are mornings the bus is late, and I don't pretend it's perfect. But for me, the trade has been overwhelmingly worth it. Give it an honest month; you might surprise yourself.",
