          "body": "After twenty winters of wrestling with a heavy gas snowblower, I switched this year to a battery-powered model, the Frostguard E20. After clearing my driveway through a dozen storms, I have thoughts worth sharing with anyone considering the change.\n\nThe best surprises were the quiet and the convenience. There is no pull cord, no fumes, and no trips to the gas station. I press a button and it starts every time, even at minus fifteen. My neighbours no longer wake to a roar at six in the morning, which alone has improved relations on my street.\n\nIt is also lighter than my old machine, so my back thanks me. For a typical two-car driveway and the light, fluffy snow we usually get, it does the job well.\n\nHere is the honest catch. On the morning after a wet, heavy dump of thirty centimetres, the battery ran flat before I finished, and the machine struggled to throw the dense snow far. If you face regular deep storms, keep a second battery charged, or this may not be the tool for you.\n\nFor most homeowners, though, I would recommend it without hesitation."
